    '<h2>The Importance of Proximity for Medical Transit</h2><p>Traveling for medical reasons is highly stressful. When visiting <strong>Nemcare Hospital</strong> or the <strong>Guwahati Medical College and Hospital (GMCH)</strong>, the last thing patients or their families need to worry about is navigating heavy traffic on GS Road. Locating a hotel situated within walking distance is critical.</p><h3>Why Choose Hotel New Ganga?</h3><p>Located immediately below the Bhangagarh bridge on GS Road, Hotel New Ganga stands practically adjacent to Nemcare Hospital (a rapid 0.3km walk). Not only does this guarantee immediate transit during medical emergencies, but you also bypass the intense Guwahati city congestion completely.</p><ul><li><strong>24/7 Front Desk:</strong> Medical schedules are unpredictable. We accommodate midnight check-ins seamlessly.</li><li><strong>Complete Sanitization:</strong> Our rooms undergo deep hygienic cleaning, crucial for post-op patients.</li><li><strong>Peace & Quiet:</strong> Heavy soundproofing ensures a restful recovery space away from the street noise.</li></ul><p>When booking, always ensure you select accommodations that offer direct access and premium in-room dining so you can focus entirely on health and recovery.</p>',
