    'Finding an affordable yet premium stay near major medical facilities like Nemcare and GMCH does not have to be hard. Follow these expert booking tips.',
    '<h2>Navigate the Guwahati Hotel Market Like a Pro</h2><p>Guwahati is the medical hub of North-East India. Consequently, demand for rooms in areas like Bhangagarh (home to Nemcare and GMCH) is constantly skyrocketing. Unfortunately, many travelers fall into traps paying surge pricing on aggregator websites.</p><h3>Booking Direct vs. OTAs</h3><p>While websites like Agoda or MakeMyTrip are convenient, they charge hotels massive commissions (upwards of 20%). As a result, budget hotels rarely list their actual best prices on these apps.</p><p>Here is the ultimate insider trick: <strong>Book Direct.</strong></p><ul><li>Call the hotel directly or use their official website booking engine.</li><li>Hotages like <strong>Hotel New Ganga</strong> will often provide exclusive discounts or waive early check-in fees for patients booking directly.</li><li>You gain access to the exact room layout you need—crucial when requesting ground-floor access or elevators for medical mobility.</li></ul><p>By leveraging direct booking networks and communicating your medical transit needs, you can secure premium, high-speed Wi-Fi, and fully air-conditioned rooms at drastically reduced rates.</p>',
